h3. Summary

When creating a content indexed property with key : value pairs such as:

{{content.property[source].id = 43928tasjdhfksa2384}}

And trying to search it with REST Call:

{code}
GET /wiki/rest/api/content/search?cql=space+%3D+DEV3+and+content.property%5Bsource%5D.id%3D43928tasjdhfksa2384&start=0
{code}

Response is:
{code}
{
"statusCode": 400,
"data": {
"authorized": false,
"valid": true,
"errors": [],
"successful": false
},
"message": "Unrecognised clause at : tasjdhfksa2384"
}
{code}

h3. Workaround
None

Cannot create children display macro with excerpt type= "Rich Content" using REST API.

Steps to reproduce:
- Create a new page
- using any tool execute REST request:
{code}
{
"version": {
"number": 2
},
"title": "Does it work?",
"type": "page",
"body": {
"storage": {
"value": "<ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"children\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"style\">h1</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name=\"page\"><ac:link><ri:page ri:content-title=\"ABCDEF\"/></ac:link></ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name=\"sort\">creation</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name=\"excerpt\">true</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name=\"excerptType\">rich_content</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro>",
"representation": "storage"
}
}
}
{code}

h3. Expected result: 
Children display macro created with excerpt type= "Rich Content"

h3. Actual result: 
Children display macro created with excerpt type= "Simple"


h3. Workaround
Manually change the excerpt type on the page
